description:
* { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; } 
body { 
 font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; 
 font-size: 15px; 
 color: #333; 
 background: #fff; 
 line-height: 1.6; 
} 
a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; } 
/* ───── OVERVIEW ───── */ 
.overview-block { 
 max-width: 1200px; 
 margin: 0 auto; 
 padding: 48px 40px 32px; 
 border-bottom: 1px solid #e8e8e8; 
} 
.overview-block h2 { 
 font-size: 13px; 
 font-weight: 700; 
 letter-spacing: 2px; 
 text-transform: uppercase; 
 margin-bottom: 14px; 
} 
.overview-block p { 
 font-size: 15px; 
 color: #444; 
 line-height: 1.8; 
 max-width: 860px; 
} 
/* ───── FEATURE SECTIONS ───── */ 
.feature-section { 
 max-width: 1200px; 
 margin: 0 auto; 
 padding: 0 40px; 
 border-bottom: 1px solid #e8e8e8; 
} 
/* Text + Image layout (default: text left, image right) */ 
.feature-row { 
 display: flex; 
 align-items: center; 
 gap: 60px; 
 padding: 56px 0; 
} 
.feature-row.img-left { flex-direction: row-reverse; } 
.feature-text { 
 flex: 1; 
 min-width: 0; 
} 
.feature-text h2 { 
 font-size: 26px; 
 font-weight: 700; 
 color: #1a1a1a; 
 margin-bottom: 16px; 
 line-height: 1.3; 
} 
.feature-text p { 
 font-size: 14.5px; 
 color: #555; 
 line-height: 1.8; 
 margin-bottom: 16px; 
} 
.feature-text .feature-label { 
 display: inline-block; 
 font-size: 12px; 
 font-weight: 700; 
 color: #15A7DC; 
 border: 1px solid #15A7DC; 
 padding: 5px 14px; 
 border-radius: 2px; 
 margin-top: 4px; 
} 
.feature-text .feature-label a { 
 color: #15A7DC; 
} 
.feature-logo { 
 height: 32px; 
 margin-bottom: 12px; 
 display: block; 
} 
.feature-media { 
 flex: 0 0 52%; 
 max-width: 52%; 
} 
.feature-media img { 
 width: 100%; 
 display: block; 
 border-radius: 4px; 
} 
.feature-media video { 
 width: 100%; 
 display: block; 
 border-radius: 4px; 
 background: #000; 
} 
/* Full-width image feature */ 
.feature-full { 
 padding: 56px 0 48px; 
} 
.feature-full h2 { 
 font-size: 26px; 
 font-weight: 700; 
 color: #1a1a1a; 
 margin-bottom: 16px; 
} 
.feature-full p { 
 font-size: 14.5px; 
 color: #555; 
 line-height: 1.8; 
 margin-bottom: 20px; 
 max-width: 760px; 
} 
.feature-full .feature-label { 
 display: inline-block; 
 font-size: 12px; 
 font-weight: 700; 
 color: #15A7DC; 
 border: 1px solid #15A7DC; 
 padding: 5px 14px; 
 border-radius: 2px; 
 margin-bottom: 24px; 
} 
.feature-full img { 
 width: 100%; 
 display: block; 
 border-radius: 4px; 
} 
.cert-logos { 
 display: flex; 
 gap: 20px; 
 align-items: center; 
 flex-wrap: wrap; 
 margin-bottom: 20px; 
} 
.cert-logos img { height: 44px; object-fit: contain; } 
@media (max-width: 900px) { 
 .hero-wrap { flex-direction: column; padding: 20px; } 
 .gallery-panel { flex: none; max-width: 100%; width: 100%; } 
 .info-panel { padding: 24px 0 0; } 
 .feature-row, .feature-row.img-left { flex-direction: column; gap: 28px; padding: 36px 0; } 
 .feature-media { flex: none; max-width: 100%; width: 100%; } 
 .acc-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } 
 .dl-groups { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } 
 .io-list { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } 
} 




 Overview 
 Bring energy-efficient performance to your classroom with the ViewBoard® IFP51 Series, available in sizes from 55 to 98 to suit any setup. Seamless interactivity is at your fingertips, thanks to its ultra-responsive 50-point touch technology and instant 'write away' annotation. Powered by Android 14 and EDLA-Certified, it offers secure access to Google Play apps, while NFC and SSO sign-in ensure instant access to personalized settings. Integrated ViewSonic Education Software completes the experience with tools for whiteboarding, casting, and device management—delivering a more dynamic and efficient teaching experience. 

 Write with Precision 
 Keep lessons flowing with ultra-responsive writing that feels as natural as pen on paper. With 50 touch points, advanced palm rejection, and anti-fingerprint coating, every stroke is smooth, clean, and lag-free. And with the floating annotation feature activated, notes stay locked in place as you scroll*, keeping key points always right where you need them. 
 * The floating annotation feature will be available in Q3 2025. 
 Write Away & 50 Touch Points with Palm Rejection 





 Tap In and Start Teaching 
 Step into the classroom and get straight to teaching. With options like NFC one-touch sign-in and SSO, your cloud-stored personalized settings, files, and profiles load instantly—no juggling passwords, no delays, just a seamless start to every lesson. 
 NFC & SSO Sign-In Options 


 Advanced Security to Safeguard Your Data 
 Enjoy peace of mind with built-in advanced security features unlocked by the EDLA certification—including automatic updates, Google Play Protect, data encryption, and two-way authentication—so classroom data stays protected and accessible only to authorized users. 
 EDLA-Certified 


 Expand Learning with Google Play 
 Get native access to fully functional Google apps like Docs and Slides with the familiar interface you know and trust. Plus, bring lessons to life with hands-on experiences that keep students engaged—from interactive science tools to language apps and music platforms—thanks to thousands of educational resources on the Google Play Store. 
 Google Workspace for Education 


 Make Every Lesson Interactive 
 Turn passive learning into active engagement with myViewBoard. Designed to adapt to any teaching style, its intuitive tools—like the infinite canvas, Spotlight, Immersive Reader, split-whiteboard Participation Mode, and AI-powered handwriting prediction—create a fluid whiteboarding experience where participation feels effortless. 
 myViewBoard Digital Whiteboard 


 Cast Wirelessly, Share Seamlessly 
 Take control of screen sharing with AirSync. Cast up to four devices at once for collaborative learning, while Moderation Mode lets you decide what goes on the big screen. Plus, with Touchback Control, you're free to roam the room, interact with students anywhere, and keep lessons dynamic. 
 AirSync Wireless Casting 





 Power Through with Fast Performance 
 Keep lessons flowing with an octa-core processor and 16GB RAM. Jump between apps, multitask, and stream content effortlessly—all with rapid responsiveness. 


 Streamline Connectivity with Triple USB-C 
 Power up, plug in, and teach without limits with triple USB-C ports. Delivering up to 65W of power, these ports keep devices charged and connected effortlessly. A top-mounted port makes webcam setup a breeze, while front- and rear-facing ports put quick connections at your fingertips. 


 Immerse Every Student in Powerful Audio 
 Keep every voice heard with an advanced 8-mic array featuring noise suppression, echo cancellation, and automatic gain control. Paired with a 70W audio system—dual 25W front-facing speakers and a 20W subwoofer—it delivers immersive sound that keeps lessons engaging. 


 Simplify Display Management 
 Take full control of device management with ViewSonic Manager. From one intuitive dashboard, you can remotely manage apps, update firmware, and instantly broadcast multimedia messages. Plus, with real-time energy monitoring, remote screen on/off control, and ECO mode scheduling, optimizing energy usage has never been easier. 
 Note: The optional Advanced license is required for multimedia broadcasts and ECO mode control. Real-time energy monitoring will be available from H2 2025. 
 Manager Remote Device Management
